==English==
===Etymology===
Spanish ''Quixote'' (''[[w:Don Quixote|Don Quixote]]'' - a character in a novel by [[w:Miguel Cervantes|Miguel Cervantes]].<!-- or is it borrowed from a spanish adjective derived from the name of the character? -->) + ''[[-ic]]''

===Adjective===
'''quixotic'''

#Desire to do [[noble]] and [[romantic]] deeds, without thought of realism and practicality.
#[[Impulsive]].
#Like [[Don Quixote]]; romantic to extravagance; absurdly [[chivalric]]; apt to be deluded.

